snippet.textDisplay:
To the ladies with "daddy issues," from a woman who has struggled with those same issues who empathizes with you so incredibly much -
Every person and situation is different, but in some situations it IS possible to mend that relationship with your pops. As a woman that was the child of an alcoholic with a bad temper, I understand that childhood can hold a lot of trauma and can result in PTSD. A technique my therapist used with me was setting an empty chair in the room with us and led me through an exercise where I talked to my dad about all of the things that I held in for years. Also you can write a lengthy letter and tear it up after, or send it even if you want to reach out that olive branch. I won't get the time that I lost with my dad back, and those memories (or lack thereof because trauma) will always be there, and it took years to get to where it was manageable. I always wanted my dad to walk me down the aisle at my wedding, and due to that hard work it happened for me. I got my father daughter dance. It IS possible; it is just ridiculously hard.
